70
00:02:01,477 --> 00:02:06,601
I prepared a statement because I want to make sure that I get everything that I want to say.

71
00:02:07,161 --> 00:02:10,224
So my daughter is a third grade student at the Roberts Elementary.

72
00:02:10,384 --> 00:02:12,145
I'm an active parent at that school.

73
00:02:12,705 --> 00:02:16,348
I appeared before this body in the spring to request funds for our mosaic mural.

74
00:02:17,008 --> 00:02:21,992
I helped run some of the enrichment nights at the school and the after school enrichment program for the PTO.

75
00:02:22,572 --> 00:02:24,334
So I'm very invested in the school.

76
00:02:25,334 --> 00:02:29,598
At the last school committee meeting, there were questions about the classes at the Roberts.

77
00:02:30,518 --> 00:02:37,965
And a comment was made that Mr. Johnson distributed his special needs students differently than other schools and no one knew why.

78
00:02:39,246 --> 00:02:43,429
So I wanted to explain a little bit and ask for some help from this group.

79
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:47,913
The Roberts Elementary has the highest enrollment of all the elementary schools in our city.

80
00:02:48,694 --> 00:02:54,879
It also houses the welcome program for the English language learners, meaning those with no English skills, and our autism program.

81
00:02:55,838 --> 00:03:02,842
These are two very large programs, 92 and 75, respectively, as of September 16th, but these numbers are constantly changing.

82
00:03:03,722 --> 00:03:06,484
To put that into perspective, it is divided equally by grade.

83
00:03:06,524 --> 00:03:11,586
We would have 15.3 ELL students per grade and 12.5 autistic children per grade, so 17% ELL and 14% autistic.

84
00:03:11,626 --> 00:03:12,647
We also have 51% low income.

85
00:03:19,637 --> 00:03:28,964
On September 9th, our total population was reported at 547, but as of September 16th, it had already climbed to 555 and is perhaps even higher now.

86
00:03:30,205 --> 00:03:32,087
Conversely, the Brooks Elementary has 449.

87
00:03:34,208 --> 00:03:42,895
It was noted at the last meeting that the two middle schools, the one that housed the ELL population was deliberately kept smaller as new students enter the program constantly.

88
00:03:43,455 --> 00:03:47,979
The same is true at the Roberts, but we do not have the buffer of being the smallest elementary school with the largest.

89
00:03:49,108 --> 00:03:57,311
Our ELL students are taken out of class to receive specialized services to help them to learn English, so they are grouped in the same class in order to accommodate scheduling.

90
00:03:57,971 --> 00:04:04,053
Imagine trying to keep five third grade classes on identical schedules to pull ELL students out of each one.

91
00:04:06,098 --> 00:04:10,362
Our higher needs autism students are also placed together because some of them share an aid.

92
00:04:10,802 --> 00:04:16,106
It was made pretty clear at budget time that there's no appetite on this committee to have an aid in each class.

93
00:04:16,747 --> 00:04:19,129
I do think that this process needs a deeper look.

94
00:04:20,490 --> 00:04:23,452
My daughter has found herself in the autism inclusion class this year.

95
00:04:24,353 --> 00:04:28,556
I understand that there are some in the other classes, but there are higher needs students in her class.

96
00:04:29,337 --> 00:04:32,599
The children at the Roberts are the most empathetic children that you will ever meet.

97
00:04:33,578 --> 00:04:39,020
But the things my daughter has been exposed to since school started at this class has given me pause.

98
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,021
Something must be done for these children.

99
00:04:42,162 --> 00:04:51,185
The teacher and aide in this class have been hit, furniture has been thrown, the classroom has been evacuated, and children have been physically restrained on almost a daily basis.

100
00:04:52,106 --> 00:04:53,366
Who is benefiting from this?

101
00:04:53,966 --> 00:04:58,028
Not the special needs children forced into a mainstream setting that is clearly overwhelming,

102
00:04:58,539 --> 00:05:01,482
not the quote standard students who are witnessing these events.

103
00:05:02,102 --> 00:05:07,487
None of them are receiving an appropriate education as all learning must cease when one of these episodes begin.

104
00:05:08,728 --> 00:05:13,872
But when I tried to discuss the wild stories that my child was coming home with, I hit a wall of privacy issues.

105
00:05:14,513 --> 00:05:21,799
If my child, any child, is being exposed to incidences that are traumatic and are violent in nature, the parents need to be notified.

106
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:25,122
Parents should not hear these stories from their children.

107
00:05:26,352 --> 00:05:27,874
and hear nothing from the school.

108
00:05:28,755 --> 00:05:31,098
We want to help our children to process what is happening.

109
00:05:31,378 --> 00:05:33,081
We are empathetic to all of the children.

110
00:05:33,581 --> 00:05:35,564
All of the children in this situation need help.

111
00:05:36,926 --> 00:05:38,488
Is this unique to my child's class?

112
00:05:39,108 --> 00:05:39,689
I think no.

113
00:05:39,829 --> 00:05:42,232
Is this an appropriate setting for any of these children?

114
00:05:42,913 --> 00:05:43,614
Absolutely no.

115
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:50,093
It is time that we stop acting as if the population of the Roberts as the same as at the other schools.

116
00:05:50,733 --> 00:05:55,356
Our school houses two high needs groups and the largest child population in the city.

117
00:05:55,976 --> 00:05:59,298
One of these programs should be shifted to a school with a lower population.

118
00:05:59,866 --> 00:06:08,756
If our class sizes were closer to the 15 to 16 mark that some of the elementary schools have, we would be able to have smaller classes for our autistic population.

119
00:06:09,256 --> 00:06:15,022
We could easily bring their class size down to 8 to 10 with no negative impact on any other classes.

120
00:06:15,683 --> 00:06:19,607
But as it stands, in order to try and bring a second grade class total

121
00:06:20,450 --> 00:06:27,856
Down from the 22 average for the autism emerging class, we were forced to have one class have a total of 24 students.

122
00:06:28,497 --> 00:06:32,100
As a comparison, the second grade class at the Brooks has an average of 17.25.

123
00:06:34,542 --> 00:06:39,206
My daughter is in grade three, which has five classrooms and an average class size of 19.8.

124
00:06:41,848 --> 00:06:45,612
Across town, the Brooks has four third grade classes with an average class size of 17.5.

125
00:06:48,460 --> 00:06:57,267
This population difference will only intensify when some of the 800 plus units permanent or under construction for the Roberts and McGlynn Elementary School begin to hold residents.

126
00:06:58,388 --> 00:07:00,510
The needs of all the children need to be considered.

127
00:07:00,650 --> 00:07:01,871
I care about all of them.

128
00:07:02,592 --> 00:07:03,272
I work with them.

129
00:07:03,893 --> 00:07:09,958
So I'm floored by the natural and easy way that they take care of each other and I'm asking the school department to step in and help them.

130
00:07:11,109 --> 00:07:17,973
My own daughter is suffering greatly as a result of her exposure in these classes, and I'm still finding out what she's witnessed in small pieces.

131
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:28,618
She's confided in my parents, in the parents of some of her friends, and some in my husband and I. The first thing she told me was that she was worried for the children that were having the incidents.

132
00:07:29,138 --> 00:07:31,140
The second thing she told me was that she was afraid.

133
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,661
No child should be afraid to go to school.

134
00:07:35,787 --> 00:07:40,550
Upon hearing that, I started a crusade to help my child and the other children in her class or classes like hers.

135
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:43,051
I spoke to the teacher who directed me to the principal.

136
00:07:43,471 --> 00:07:53,977
I spoke to the principal, and other than the incident that required a student to leave by ambulance, he had heard of no other incidences, nor had the school department, nor the special needs department.

137
00:07:54,734 --> 00:07:55,014
Why?

138
00:07:56,075 --> 00:07:58,556
I suspect it is because nothing will come of reporting it.

139
00:07:59,317 --> 00:08:02,239
But despite my reporting it, nothing has come of it yet.

140
00:08:02,759 --> 00:08:12,885
The adjustment counselor at the school has not even spoken to the children about the incident that was reported and happened a week ago, an incident that required an ambulance to remove a student from the school.

141
00:08:13,246 --> 00:08:14,647
The parents have not been notified.

142
00:08:15,327 --> 00:08:16,308
What is the protocol?

143
00:08:16,768 --> 00:08:21,031
What measures are in place to help these autistic children who are suffering or the other students?

144
00:08:21,871 --> 00:08:24,492
My daughter is refusing to go back into that classroom.

145
00:08:25,012 --> 00:08:28,493
We have been attempting to help her cope with what she has witnessed almost daily.

146
00:08:29,253 --> 00:08:30,894
She has been having migraine headaches.

147
00:08:31,254 --> 00:08:32,334
She's extremely anxious.

148
00:08:32,794 --> 00:08:36,495
This weekend, she had a panic attack, thinking about having to go back to class.

149
00:08:37,676 --> 00:08:46,839
She reports that her teachers have assured her that they will keep the children safe, and they neither need to worry nor be afraid because they will worry and be afraid for them.

150
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:51,060
My daughter's takeaway from that statement is that the incidents will continue.

151
00:08:52,187 --> 00:08:54,968
that there will still be danger and that she's just supposed to ignore it.

152
00:08:56,508 --> 00:08:57,368
So please help us.

153
00:08:58,508 --> 00:09:01,329
I understand that there's privacy issues, but something has to be done.

154
00:09:01,769 --> 00:09:05,990
The teachers and Mr. Johnson are doing the best that they can with the tools available to them.

155
00:09:06,370 --> 00:09:07,470
They need more tools.

156
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:12,971
They need a smaller population so they can adjust class sizes to accommodate the high needs of our children.

157
00:09:13,591 --> 00:09:18,392
We can't only worry about my one child, but I am worried about my child.

158
00:09:18,735 --> 00:09:20,456
We need to worry about all of the children.

159
00:09:20,756 --> 00:09:22,817
The needs of all the children are not identical.

160
00:09:26,278 --> 00:09:26,578
Thanks.

161
00:09:26,918 --> 00:09:27,259
Thank you.

162
00:09:27,279 --> 00:09:29,580
Mr. Superintendent.

163
00:09:32,101 --> 00:09:34,742
So we met with Mrs. Rodriguez this morning.

164
00:09:35,502 --> 00:09:36,703
We went over all these things.

165
00:09:36,743 --> 00:09:38,743
We've prepared some materials for you.

166
00:09:38,763 --> 00:09:45,526
I'm going to call upon our special needs director and our assistant for elementary education to speak to the issues.

167
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:47,147
There is a lot going on.

168
00:09:48,344 --> 00:09:50,064
There's a lot going on of response.

169
00:09:50,625 --> 00:09:53,485
Occasionally, in a given classroom, there's going to be some disruption.

170
00:09:54,706 --> 00:09:59,267
The year starts, some youngsters express themselves, and then we respond to it.

171
00:09:59,907 --> 00:10:08,529
When information comes to us, that classroom's been visited multiple times by both Diane and by Kathy, and there's some plans in place.

172
00:10:09,330 --> 00:10:10,790
So I don't believe it's undoable.

173
00:10:11,370 --> 00:10:14,891
I believe the Roberts does have some population issues, but so don't the other schools.

174
00:10:14,911 --> 00:10:18,052
If you're at the Columbus, you have the therapeutic learning program.

175
00:10:18,573 --> 00:10:20,654
At other schools, you have other programs that are there.

176
00:10:21,974 --> 00:10:25,015
Some years, the Brooks has had more people than the Roberts.

177
00:10:25,095 --> 00:10:27,355
In some years, the McGlynn has had more people than the Roberts.

178
00:10:27,735 --> 00:10:30,496
Population shifts are by geography to some degree.

179
00:10:31,336 --> 00:10:39,898
But having said that, let me ask Diane and Kathy to come up and talk a little bit about the specifics that Mrs. Rodriguez has raised.

180
00:10:40,418 --> 00:10:43,839
And I want to make it very clear, we're very concerned when things happen.

181
00:10:44,139 --> 00:10:45,539
We're not unconcerned.

182
00:10:46,059 --> 00:10:48,160
That's not a fair assessment of what goes on.

183
00:10:48,996 --> 00:10:49,756
but let them speak.

184
00:10:51,316 --> 00:10:51,757
Good evening.

185
00:10:52,597 --> 00:11:04,239
So I prepared a quick report for you to read just to let you know about the incidences that did happen at the Roberts Elementary School in that particular third grade classroom.

186
00:11:04,939 --> 00:11:09,680
We do have some children who are special needs children and some ELL students in that classroom.

187
00:11:12,241 --> 00:11:17,422
Two students that we are aware of exhibited loud and aggressive behaviors.

188
00:11:17,903 --> 00:11:21,804
that required interventions through the safety care support team.

189
00:11:22,725 --> 00:11:30,507
Neither of the students that we are discussing who had these incidences are special education students, and I think I need to make that clear.

190
00:11:31,568 --> 00:11:38,650
Prior to the start of school, staff were not aware of any factors that would have helped them anticipate the behaviors of these students.

191
00:11:39,510 --> 00:11:47,633
Both of them are linked to community supports, and staff is working to obtain information to expedite an educational evaluation.

192
00:11:48,750 --> 00:11:55,374
The third grade teacher has been working very closely with the safety care team to address the needs of these children.

193
00:11:56,215 --> 00:12:05,621
Mr. Johnson reviewed the school year mandates during the first weeks of school, such as he discussed de-escalation strategies and staying calm.

194
00:12:06,921 --> 00:12:12,565
When the high intensity behaviors occurred in this classroom, students were evacuated

195
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:18,764
to the safety care team so that the safety care team could triage the situation.

196
00:12:20,105 --> 00:12:27,230
The evacuations framed as academic movement opportunities for the children in the building, in that classroom.

197
00:12:28,030 --> 00:12:32,974
More intensive incidences were not witnessed by the children, to my knowledge.

198
00:12:34,414 --> 00:12:37,935
The Roberts School does have a lot of support in their building.

199
00:12:38,576 --> 00:12:41,737
They have 19 safety care trained staff.

200
00:12:42,317 --> 00:12:50,780
They have a full-time BCBA, a .5 school psychologist, and there's a full-time school adjustment counselor as well in the building.

201
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:54,842
We do need to respect the privacy of the students.

202
00:12:55,382 --> 00:13:02,445
We understand that this can be disruptive to the class, and we know that it can lead to disrupting the learning process.

203
00:13:03,725 --> 00:13:22,984
After speaking with the teacher, and I have been down to the Roberts School three times since the very first incident, she has assured me that she is on par with whatever she's teaching in English, literacy, math, and reading, and she does give her children homework.

204
00:13:24,111 --> 00:13:27,452
We are organizing the following procedures for these children.

205
00:13:28,172 --> 00:13:31,333
We're conducting risk threat assessments.

206
00:13:32,033 --> 00:13:35,154
We will perform full evaluations of the students.

207
00:13:36,134 --> 00:13:40,595
We're looking at creating an abbreviated schedules when the students return.

208
00:13:41,496 --> 00:13:44,956
We will discuss and meet with community organizations.

209
00:13:45,557 --> 00:13:47,077
We will meet with the parents.

210
00:13:47,777 --> 00:13:50,138
And we will provide additional support

211
00:13:51,090 --> 00:13:53,011
in that classroom if need be.

212
00:13:53,871 --> 00:14:03,135
I think Mrs. Rodriguez knows me especially well enough to know that we will get things in place as soon as possible.

213
00:14:03,755 --> 00:14:15,841
The teachers, the support staff, the assistant principal and the principal along with Kathy and I have been working diligently since we found out the information.

214
00:14:17,341 --> 00:14:18,822
Safety is something that

215
00:14:19,457 --> 00:14:25,899
we definitely is first and foremost because children can't learn unless they feel safe in a classroom.

216
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:32,862
Um, I've discussed this with miss Rodriguez and she knows now that the plan is in place to move forward.

217
00:14:34,082 --> 00:14:43,486
Kathy, is that, um, yeah, so I just like to mention around the enrollment of special education students at the Roberts is consistent with other buildings.

218
00:14:43,626 --> 00:14:46,467
And in fact, a couple of the other buildings are a little bit higher.

219
00:14:47,532 --> 00:14:55,893
I believe the McGlynn has a few more students than over at the Roberts, but it is consistent across all of the schools, all of the elementary schools.

220
00:15:00,099 --> 00:15:00,259
Ms.

221
00:15:00,279 --> 00:15:00,639
Cuno.

222
00:15:01,479 --> 00:15:01,920
Thank you.

223
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:02,680
Thank you, Ms.

224
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:06,041
Rodriguez, to inform us of this situation.

225
00:15:06,441 --> 00:15:22,546
I guess one of the questions I have is that I appreciate everybody doing this diligently the minute you found out about it, but I guess what goes back to me is the fact of if we have children, whether or not they were in the vicinity or not, rumors start.

226
00:15:22,726 --> 00:15:26,607
One story, you know, is a domino effect and becomes a larger story.

227
00:15:27,087 --> 00:15:49,564
So I guess for me is why weren't parents informed of not necessarily giving out the information because of confidentiality and things like that, but if the students were talking about this incident that occurred and then they went home and they were telling their parents, why wasn't something like at least sent out saying, you know, we understand what happened.

228
00:15:49,884 --> 00:15:50,925
