805
01:03:34,840 --> 01:03:36,961
So SBIRT is a verbal screening tool.

806
01:03:37,301 --> 01:03:38,742
It's evidence-based.

807
01:03:38,822 --> 01:03:40,003
It's used with adolescents.

808
01:03:40,403 --> 01:03:44,005
And it's administered during a private one-to-one conversation.

809
01:03:44,586 --> 01:03:47,327
It consists of a few questions.

810
01:03:48,008 --> 01:03:58,794
And the goal is to promote prevention and identify early those students whose patterns of drug or alcohol use are presenting, putting their health at risk.

811
01:03:59,615 --> 01:04:03,597
Use of the tool allows the screener to determine a level of risk.

812
01:04:04,616 --> 01:04:14,698
For students who have a very low level of risk, the screener will support and encourage their positive, healthy decision making and lifestyle.

813
01:04:15,919 --> 01:04:25,741
For students who screen higher level of risk, the screener will either provide a brief intervention or the highest level would provide referral to treatment.

814
01:04:26,281 --> 01:04:28,341
So it's a tiered level of approach.

815
01:04:31,250 --> 01:04:35,872
The screening entails students meeting with a trained screener.

816
01:04:36,292 --> 01:04:37,372
They meet one-to-one.

817
01:04:37,412 --> 01:04:42,254
We are taking them out of either health ed or physical education classes.

818
01:04:42,934 --> 01:04:59,680
And the screener will go through the six questions and then make a decision on whether it's just that we're saying, great, you're doing a wonderful job, you're making good choices, or probing a little bit further with the students.

819
01:05:01,040 --> 01:05:07,104
Students and parents have the option of opting out by submitting a letter.

820
01:05:07,124 --> 01:05:16,050
And we will be notifying parents during the fall that we will be starting these screenings.

